# World Horse Organization

Read `OUTLINE.md` at the repo root before making product or architecture decisions.

## Tech stack

- Next.js 16 (App Router, Turbopack), TypeScript, ply-css + Tailwind 4 (migrating to ply)
- Drizzle ORM → Neon Postgres (via Vercel integration)
- Auth.js v5 (Google OAuth), DrizzleAdapter
- Deployed on Vercel at worldhorseorganization.org

## Key paths

- `lib/db/schema.ts` — single source of truth for all tables and enums
- `lib/auth/config.ts` — Auth.js setup, includes `createUser` event for signup seeding
- `lib/horses/generate.ts` — horse stat generation (bell curve)
- `lib/horses/seed.ts` — signup bonus + starter horse
- `lib/races/simulate.ts` — race simulation engine (stats + randomness)
- `app/horse-racing/*` — authenticated game routes (protected by middleware)
- `app/api/horses/` — horse CRUD endpoints
- `app/api/races/` — race CRUD, entry, and simulation endpoints
- `app/api/weeks/` — week management endpoints
- `lib/db/ledger.ts` — atomic debit/credit helpers for the balance ledger

## Language rules

Horses are never "owned." Users are guardians, not owners.

| Wrong              | Right                        |
| ------------------ | ---------------------------- |
| owner              | guardian                     |
| mint / create      | rescue                       |
| buy                | assume guardianship          |
| sell               | transfer guardianship        |
| delete / kill      | release back to the wild     |

Apply this in UI copy, variable names, API responses, and documentation.

## Monetization model (v1)

Free-to-play with optional microtransactions. In-game credits only — no real-money payouts, no withdrawals, no gambling classification. Credits are scarce and meaningful: rescuing, racing, breeding, and trading all cost credits. Profits from credit purchases fund the WHO real-world mission (first target: ending Central Park horse-drawn carriages).

## Current state

- **Phase 0 (done):** Auth, ledger (balances + transactions), deployment, domain.
- **Phase 1 (done):** Horse schema, generation, rescue flow, stable UI, detail view.
- **Phase 2 (done):** Race schema (weeks, races, entries, results), simulation engine, race UI, enter/run flow.
- **Phase 3 (done):** Stakes (place/debit credits), payout logic (pool split to 1st/2nd/3rd stakers), leaderboard.
- **Next up:** Phase 4 — guardianship trading marketplace.

## Conventions

- Server components by default; `"use client"` only when needed.
- DB queries go in server components or API routes, never client-side.
- Schema changes: edit `lib/db/schema.ts`, run `npm run db:push`.
- Keep components in `components/` grouped by domain (e.g. `horses/`, `auth/`).
